Author: jl777c#5810
Content: since atomicDEX doesnt KYC, as long as you dont link your dex address to other addresses, then there is no link to you. keeping it segregated is pretty hard especially if you need to convert to fiat. zaddr based swaps will help immensely with privacy, and PIRATE will be the most private haven for funds

Author: JimD#9272
Content: Would sending BTC to coinbase from a DEX count as linking it my dex address ?

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: yes

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: but if you had 2 dex addresses you could intervene a BTC <-> PIRATE and PIRATE <-> BTC swap

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: the ending BTC address being a never used address. there wont be a direct way to correlate, but this requires a lot of other such swaps so simply detecting you are doing this wouldnt be easy
